# pyHMT2D Project Overview

pyHMT2D is a Python package for controlling and automating 2D hydraulic modeling, with support for pre- and post-processing simulation results. The package currently supports:

- SRH-2D (USBR)
- HEC-RAS (USACE)
- Backwater-1D (demonstration model)

## Key Components

The main package structure is organized as follows:

- [pyHMT2D/](mdc:pyHMT2D) - Core package directory
  - [__init__.py](mdc:pyHMT2D/__init__.py) - Package initialization
  - [__about__.py](mdc:pyHMT2D/__about__.py) - Package metadata
  - [__common__.py](mdc:pyHMT2D/__common__.py) - Common utilities
  - [Calibration/](mdc:pyHMT2D/Calibration) - Model calibration tools
  - [Parametric_Study/](mdc:pyHMT2D/Parametric_Study) - Parametric study tools
  - [cli/](mdc:pyHMT2D/cli) - Command-line interface
  - [Hydraulic_Models_Data/](mdc:pyHMT2D/Hydraulic_Models_Data) - Model data handling
  - [Misc/](mdc:pyHMT2D/Misc) - Miscellaneous utilities

## Key Features

1. Model Control and Automation
   - Batch simulations
   - Model calibration
   - Monte-Carlo simulations

2. Data Processing
   - Reading model results into NumPy arrays
   - Converting results to VTK format
   - Sampling and probing simulation results

3. Model Interoperability
   - Converting between SRH-2D and HEC-RAS formats
   - Mesh and boundary condition conversion
   - Result comparison tools

4. Visualization and Analysis
   - VTK-based visualization
   - Result analysis tools
   - Terrain data manipulation

## Getting Started

1. Installation:
   ```bash
   pip install pyHMT2D
   ```

2. Basic Usage:
   ```python
   import pyHMT2D
   ```

3. Documentation:
   - See [docs/](mdc:docs) for detailed documentation
   - Check [examples/](mdc:examples) for usage examples

